{"TopicId":160102,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do you place wheels on abomination like this?","CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:10:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:10:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know this isn\u0027t some kind of revultionary design and I\u0027ll probably scrap it but if there is something like this, how does one attach wheels? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://postimg.org/image/lujvsehbz/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002220170502230803_1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://s19.postimg.org/riq6jaloj/20170502230803_1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-02T21:27:43Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2017 09:27  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Numerlor\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCarefully and hopefully.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Urses","CreatedById":175990,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:20:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you try a quadriped with stearable back axis? I know not the mass but the biggest landinggears at side gonduls up front and paired mediums at the back for stearing on the ground. If you are able to stear with your tailwings and maybe \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E than switch the backwards one for large and front one for giant versions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFunny Kabooms\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUrses\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-03T18:13:59Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2017 06:13  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Urses\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"regex","CreatedById":70807,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:52:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThrow some girders and struts on it to match the desired wheel placement.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nE: Even better, create a launch carriage you can jettison right after takeoff. Then place wheels on\u00A0the other parts so they can land independently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-02T21:55:37Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2017 09:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by regex\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cubinator","CreatedById":150330,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T21:58:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlace a wheel on any part of the ship that you think might come into contact with the ground, including nose, tail fin and wing ends, bottom and top. Otherwise you\u0027ll never know for sure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-02T21:59:16Z\u0022 title=\u002205/02/2017 09:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 2, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by cubinator\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T22:12:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like you have an uncrewed, airbreathing assist stage to help the main crewed part get to orbit, right?\u00A0 Well, one alternative is to just tweak the design to make it easier to put wheels on.\u00A0 Instead of having one big airbreather mounted underneath, what about two long/skinny airbreathers mounted on the left and right sides of the orbiter?\u00A0 That way, you can mount the landing gear on the orbiter in conventional fashion and it takes off just fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-02T23:18:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReverse it, and put that lower section on top?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T01:31:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223042862\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493761979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022regex\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, regex said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven better, create a launch carriage you can jettison right after takeoff. Then place wheels on\u00A0the other parts so they can land independently.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWithout further detail I\u0027m inclined to agree to this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDepending on how each part recovery will be handled (stage recovery /independent landing on runaway /whatever) and how each part fly/land may allow something different.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blaarkies","CreatedById":153700,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T03:54:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou have to move this problem somewhere else...specifically, attached to the bottom of an even bigger plane\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n...but really, thats half the problem. Why can\u0027t it be on top like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/151713-fourfa/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022151713\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/151713-fourfa/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@fourfa\u003C/a\u003E mentioned?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spricigo","CreatedById":166502,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T07:16:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223043137\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493783664\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022153700\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Blaarkies\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Blaarkies said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy can\u0027t it be on top like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/151713-fourfa/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022151713\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/151713-fourfa/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@fourfa\u003C/a\u003E mentioned?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m guessing there. \u00A0But assuming he is relying on those engines in the lower part for takeoff, \u00A0he don\u0027t want this unaligned thrust causing pitch down.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr maybe he just reached something that actually fly* and is concerned with the effort needed to find this \u0022equilibrium\u0022 \u00A0again if much is changed.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*even if only as in is such a abomination that the ground rejects it. \u00A0(no intention to disrespect your creation. Just sharing how I feel with my attempts with the same concept, my abominations)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ozelui","CreatedById":175470,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T16:24:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to keep the general shape, i\u0027d probably go for something similar to this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022S4uWS2I.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/S4uWS2I.jpg\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnce in the air you can detach the front landing gears. ( I\u0027m asuming the lower fuselage is going to be detached when it\u0027s bingo fuel ).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr you could turn upside down the front part of the lower fuselage, leaving the intakes closer to the ground and put the landing gears there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what i\u0027m really wondering is... how is going Jeb to get inside the cockpit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-03T16:28:21Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2017 04:28  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Ozelui\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Numerlor","CreatedById":174198,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T16:56:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223043658\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493828681\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022175470\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ozelui\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Ozelui said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what i\u0027m really wondering is... how is going Jeb to get inside the cockpit?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe \u003Ci\u003Eis\u00A0\u003C/i\u003EJeb, he can figure it out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ozelui","CreatedById":175470,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-03T18:01:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223043738\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022160102\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493830606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174198\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Numerlor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Numerlor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe \u003Ci\u003Eis\u00A0\u003C/i\u003EJeb, he can figure it out\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLol, true. I bet for a catapult of some kind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-05-03T19:44:33Z\u0022 title=\u002205/03/2017 07:44  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EMay 3, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Ozelui\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}